body:
The second remodels/kai ni of [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i]'s [[Houshou (Kancolle)|]], as seen in post #5878341 for standard kai ni and post #5878299 for E version.

Released 06 December 2022, her kai ni comes in two forms: standard kai ni and a transport "E" version. She keeps her usual [[Japanese clothes|traditional outfit]] from base form in her standard kai ni but gains a white [[hair ribbon]], large white [[sash]] ([i]these two are the most obvious changes to note if she's not depicted with her rig or in her E version[/i]), and a 28 cm [[anti-aircraft gun|rocket launcher]] on her [[quiver]], while her [[flight deck]] gains a catapult (faintly seen). 

Her "E" version swaps her base outfit in favor of a [[green kimono]] meant to represent her real-life camouflage pattern, while she holds a daihatsu amphibious landing craft.

In remodeling Houshou from kai to kai ni, a prototype catapult is required as she never received any upgrade after 1944 (when she was modified to handle heavier aircraft for training purposes), and never received any aircraft catapult.

title: uss_enterprise_(cv-6)
body:
A World War II American [i]Yorktown[/i]-class [[aircraft carrier]]. She was nicknamed "Big E", "Lucky E", "The Grey Ghost", and "The Galloping Ghost".

She fought in almost all of the battles in the Pacific Campaign and was considered a lucky ship due to surviving major damages and hardships. The [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] mistakenly believed they had sunk her on multiple occasions, only to encounter her again in later battles. She was the most decorated U.S. ship of WWII.

Subsequent attempts were made to raise enough money to buy her from the US Navy and preserve her as a museum ship, but they all failed to reach the amount of money to do so. She was scheduled for scrapping on July 1, 1958 and was completely scrapped on May 1960.

Although she does not appear in [[Kantai Collection]], multiple artists have created unofficial Kancolle-styled personifications of the ship, the most popular of which is [[Jeanex]]'s [[Enterprise (Pacific)]].

title: blood_bag
body:
A small bag full of [[blood]], which has been collected from the patient or from a blood donor in order to replace that patient's blood should there be a lot of blood loss during surgery, or from exsanguination due to a critical [[injury]].

Different patients/donors' blood is collected, analyzed and grouped according to blood type, of which there are four: "A, B, AB, and O":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_blood_group_systems, depending upon inherited antigens. There is also the + and - status to indicate if the "Rh factor":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rh_blood_group_system (or Rhesus factor) is present.

Blood bags are often seen hanging from [[iv stand|intravenous stands]] in hospitals near the patient's bed.

title: geoduck
body:
A type of saltwater [[clam]] native to the west coast of North America.

The shell of the clam ranges from 15 centimeters (5.9 in) to over 20 centimeters (7.9 in) in length, but the extremely long siphons make the clam itself much longer than this, with the siphons alone being able to reach 1 meter (3.3 ft) in length. The geoduck is one of the largest clams in the world and one of the longest-lived animals in the world, with the oldest known specimen having lived 168 years.

Rather infamous for its [[phallic_symbol|phallic]] shape, which led into it became a delicacy and are believed to have aphodisaic properties.

One class of such clothing is called "Goku Uniforms" and is divided into three categories based on how much Life Fibers they have woven into them; the more Life Fibers a Goku Uniform contains, the more powerful the wearer becomes at the risk of being overwhelmed, killed and/or consumed by the Life Fibers. title: enigma_(housamo)

Designed by [[musou_luf|MusouLuf]]

A cryptographic life form born into a space beyond the bounds of the 23 other worlds. He was deciphered by the Guild Master of the Akihabara Creators and given an outer appearance and personality for interacting with the world at large. Specifically, in accordance with the preferences of the one he calls his creator, he's taken on the form of a mechanical Therian. His true form is immaterial, however, as Enigma's existence is comprised solely of data transmitted over the net. The upshot of this is that he's capable of self-reproducing with no limits beyond those of his own available resources, and each and every copy is individually customized and optimized for the service of a specific end user. This particular Enigma has been customized for use by the Guild Master of the Summoners, considering himself to be something of a secretary for his assigned master and adopting a vaguely condescending, highly intellectual persona in service to that end. The idea, it seems, is that he quite genuinely wishes to supplement the shortcomings of his master's ego, as calculated through careful observation and data-crunching, in order to prove his worth. This is very much in keeping with his self-proclaimed role, since the very word secretary is derived from secret, having long ago been used to refer to those who safeguarded the classified documents of the aristocracyâ€”a term which perfectly and succinctly fits the identity of this cryptographic Enigma like a glove. There is one particular Transient who's quite taken with Enigma, being extremely fond of puzzles and quizzes.

title: gundam_f91
body:
[b]Mobile Suit Gundam F91[/b] (Japanese: æ©Ÿå‹•æˆ¦å£«ã‚¬ãƒ³ãƒ€ãƒ F91ãƒ•ã‚©ãƒ¼ãƒŸãƒ¥ãƒ© ãƒŠã‚¤ãƒ³ãƒ†ã‚£ãƒ¯ãƒ³, Hepburn: [i]Kidou Senshi Gandamu Foumyura Nainti Wan[/i], [b]Mobile Suit Gundam Formula 91[/b]) is a 1991 anime film set in the [[Gundam]] universe. 

It was written and directed by [[mobile_suit_gundam|original Gundam]] creator [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]]. It was Tomino's attempt to launch a new U.C. Gundam saga, set 30 years after [[Char's Counterattack]]. He re-teamed with character designer [[Yasuhiko Yoshikazu]] and [[mecha]] designer [[Ookawara Kunio]]  for the occasion.

Originally planned as a full-length television series, Gundam F91 hit a production snag due to staff disputes, and the project was stopped after the screenplays for the first thirteen episodes were written. It was then decided that what was made of the show would be condensed into a theatrical feature. The film was first released in [[Japan]] on March 16, 1991.

Set in [b]U.C. 0123[/b] (44 years after [[mobile_suit_gundam|the original Gundam]]), the story of Gundam F91 revolves around teenage space colonist [[Seabook Arno]], his girlfriend [[Cecily Fairchild]], and the efforts of the [[Crossbone Vanguard]] militia to establish an aristocracy known as "Cosmo Babylonia". In keeping with Gundam tradition, the civilian Seabook is forced by circumstance to pilot the [[F91 Gundam]], coincidentally designed in part by his estranged mother, Dr. [[Monica Arno]].

title: pluto_(manga)
body:
[b]PLUTO[/b] (ãƒ—ãƒ«ãƒ¼ãƒˆã‚¦, [i]PurÅ«tÅ[/i])  is a Japanese [[science fiction]], [[cyberpunk]] and detective manga series written and illustrated by [[Urasawa Naoki]] (of [[MONSTER (manga)|]] fame). 

It was serialized in Shogakukan's seinen manga magazine Big Comic Original from September 2003 to April 2009, with its chapters collected into eight tankÅbon volumes. The series is based on the [[Tezuka Osamu]]'s [[Tetsuwan Atom]]/[[atom (pluto)|Astro Boy]] classic manga series, specifically a reboot of "The Greatest Robot on Earth" (åœ°ä¸Šæœ€å¤§ã®ãƒ­ãƒœãƒƒãƒˆ, [i]ChijÅ Saidai no Robotto[/i]) story arc, and named after [[pluto (pluto (manga))|the arc's chief villain]]. 

Urasawa reinterprets the story as a suspenseful murder mystery starring [[Gesicht (pluto)|]], a Europol robot detective trying to solve the case of a string of [[robot]] and human deaths. 

Nagasaki Takashi is credited as the series' co-author. Tezuka Macoto, Tezuka Osamu's son, supervised the series, and Tezuka Productions is listed as having given cooperation. The series was licensed and released in English in North America by Viz Media under the name [b]PLUTO: Urasawa x Tezuka[/b]. 

PLUTO was a critical and commercial success, winning several awards, including the ninth Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize, and selling over 8.5 million copies. An original net anime series, produced by Genco and Tezuka Productions, and animated by Studio M2, premiered on [[Netflix]] in 2023.

title: fancy_island
body:
[b]lomando.com[/b], also called "[b]Fancy Island[/b]", is a point-and-click Japanese horror puzzle browser 'game', infamous for its deceptive front page, which is disguised with cute aesthetics and illustrations themed around a [[cat girl]] character. 

The game is initiated by clicking on an image of the site '[[mimi_(fancy_island)|mascot]]'. The objective is to navigate through the various 'levels', attempting to avoid countless [[jumpscare|screamers]]/monsters along the way, and defeat the 'final boss' at the end.

title: g-arcane
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] franchise. It first appeared in the [[Gundam G No Reconguista]] series from 2014.

[b]MSAM-033 Gundam G-Arcane[/b]

A prototype high performance [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by the Amerian Army. 

While the design could not compete with the [[G-Self]] due to a difference in technological expertise from the Amerians, it was nonetheless a very capable unit, usually equipped with a powerful long range [[beam rifle]] for accurate sniping. It was piloted by [[Aida Rayhunton|Aida Surugan]]. While on the Venus Globe, the unit is equipped with the Full Dress specification with additional skirt beam cannons, enabling it to become an omnidirectional force on the battlefield.

title: affliction_(darkest_dungeon)
body:
A commonly seen game mechanic in Darkest Dungeon 1 and 2, it appears over the heads of affected individuals who have succumbed to a severe negative emotion or madness. The affliction can be obtained from many of the game's stress-related mechanics and inflicts a negative effect on the afflicted individual.

It is often seen with its iconic black circular arc and five spike like protrusions, heading inwards, surrounded by a red hue floating above characters' heads to indicate they are currently plagued by said affliction. 

[spoilers]Through the many challenges that the heroes of Darkest Dungeon 2 go through, it is eventually revealed that its true name is: 'The Iron Crown', and is actually the entity responsible for causing many of Darkest Dungeon's abomination related disasters and spreading the corruption in the land.[/spoilers]

title: blade_runner
body:
A 1982 American [[science fiction]] film, directed by Ridley Scott and starring [[Harrison Ford]], [[Rutger Hauer]], [[Edward James Olmos]], [[Daryl Hannah]] and [[Sean Young]].

The screenplay, written by Hampton Fancher and David Peoples, is loosely based on the 1968 novel [[Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?]] by American sci-fi writer [[Philip K. Dick]].

While not initially a success with North American audiences, [i][b]Blade Runner[/b][/i] was very popular internationally and became a cult film. It was a hit in Japan, where it greatly influenced the "[[cyberpunk]]" look of later sci-fi anime and manga like [[Akira (manga)|]], [[Bubblegum Crisis]], [[Armitage III]], [[Ghost in the Shell]] and [[Appleseed]] among many many others. 

The movie's dark style and futuristic designs by [[Syd Mead]] have served as a benchmark and its influence can be seen in many subsequent science fiction films, anime, video games, and television programs.

A sequel called [[Blade Runner 2049]] was released in most countries on October 6, 2017. It was released in Japan on October 27, 2017.

[b]Snatcher[/b] (ã‚¹ãƒŠãƒƒãƒãƒ£ãƒ¼ [i]SunacchÄ[/i]) is a [[cyberpunk]] graphic adventure [[video game]] produced by [[Konami]], originally released in Japan for the NEC PC-8801 and MSX 2 computer platforms in 1988. 

It was followed by a CD-ROM remake released for the [[PC Engine]] video game console in 1992, which was subsequently ported and localized into English for the Mega-CD/[[Sega CD]] in 1994. 

Snatcher was the second video game written and directed by [[Kojima Hideo]], following the original [[metal_gear_(series)|Metal Gear]] for the MSX2. 

The game's futuristic story centers around a detective called [[Gillian Seed]], who is assigned to investigate a breed of [[android]]s known as "Snatchers", who are killing humans and taking their place in society. The game is known for its heavy influence from cult [[science fiction]] films such as [[Blade Runner]], [[Akira (manga)|]] and [[The Terminator]].

title: gondola
body:
A traditional passenger-carrying [[boat]] of Venice, Italy, measuring a law-regulated 10.85m in length and having an maximum breadth of 1.40m. It is often sculled by a single person standing on the rear deck, with the [[oar]] resting on an oarlock. Gondolas with multiple rowers also exist, an example being the [i]traghetto[/i] or ferry gondola. 

[i]Gondole[/i] can be differentiated from other boats by being asymmetrical, with one side being slightly longer than the other, and by the presence of a [i]ferro[/i], a stylized S-shaped bow ornament made of metal whose design represents elements of Venice and whose weight counterbalances that of the gondolier.

Gondolas figure prominently in [[Amano Kozue]]'s anime and manga series [[Aria (manga)|]].

A tree-topper or treetopper is a decorative ornament placed on the top (or "crown") of a Christmas tree. Tree-toppers can take any form, though the most common include a star (representing the Star of Bethlehem), finial, angel ("Christmas angel"), or fairy. Additional forms range from a paper rosette, ribbon bow, Father Christmas or Santa Claus, to a Christian cross, owl, white dove, spike, or sunburst.

Tree-toppers may be made of from a wide range of materials. Modern plastic tree-toppers are often electric and once connected with the tree's lights offer a gentle glow. Following World War II, various symbols of Christmastide, such as Santa Claus, were introduced as electrified tree-toppers.

title: tiger_(p)
body:
The [b]Porsche Tiger[/b], also known as the [b]VK4501(P)[/b] or [b]Tiger(P)[/b], was an unsuccessful heavy tank prototype produced by Porsche in [[Germany]] during 1942.

On the 21st May 1942 Henschel and Porsche at a meeting in Germany were asked to submit designs for a 45 ton heavy tank capable of mounting the high velocity 88mm KwK L/56 gun which was derived from the German [[88_flak|88mm flak gun]]. Both the Henschel and Porsche tanks were to be fitted with the same turret supplied by Krupp. The Porsche company worked on updating the VK3001P medium tank, Porsche's medium tank prototype, and adapted parts used on it for the new tank.

The new Porsche tank, designated the VK4501(P) was to be powered by twin air cooled gasoline Porsche Type 101/1 engines which were mounted to the rear of the tank. The twin engines would then drive two generators, one on either side of the tank, which would then power two motors which would drive the tracks. But the engine along with its drive system were very prone to break down and needed almost constant maintenance to keep the tank running. This and the tank being less maneuverable than its competitor was the reason why Henschel's prototype, the [[Tiger I]], was adopted for production instead.

Porsche AG had already manufactured about one hundred chassis of the unsuccessful Porsche Tiger that were no longer required. It was therefore decided that the Porsche chassis were to be used as the basis of a new heavy tank destroyer (the [[Elefant]]), mounting Krupp's newly developed 88 mm Pak 43/2 anti-tank gun.

body:
[b][i]Starship Troopers[/i][/b] (å®‡å®™ã®æˆ¦å£« [i]Uchuu No Senshi[/i], lit. "Soldiers of Space") is a six part anime OVA produced by Sunrise/Bandai Visual and released in 1988. It is based on the book [[Starship Troopers]] by Robert A. Heinlein that was published in 1959. 

This anime production is considered by many the "most faithful" to the original novel's plot, despite the fact that many liberties were taken with the characters and the original book's themes. For instance [[Johnny Rico]], an [[Asian]] [[philippines|Filipino]] in the novel, is a [[blonde_hair|blonde]] White [[argentina|Argentine]] in the OVA. 

Interestingly, the main character's ethnicity in the OVA series has more in common with Paul Verhoeven's 1997 film than the source material â€” this despite their productions being wholly unrelated and having nearly a decade of difference. However, unlike the 1997 film, the most prominent link the anime has to the original book are the inclusion of [[power armor]] and drop pods that were absent in Verhoeven's film.

[[Miyatake Kazutaka]] of Studio Nue originally designed the [[power suit]]s in the OVA for the Japanese edition of the 50s novel in the early 80s. The design also appeared uncredited in the [[Daicon III]] and [[Daicon IV]] fan made animated shorts in the early 80s, several years before the OVA was made.

Fumiruiru is Kuon's handmaiden and childhood friend.

Born from an union between members of two rival clans, she was left behind as a baby until [[Ulthury]] took her and, as the clans end their grudge due to her existence, was bought back to her family. It was in this state that she debuted in the original [[Utawarerumono]], making her only somewhat older than Kuon.

In her adulthood, with her talents and Urtoriy's tutelage, Fumiruiru became a very proficient mage and healer. With her beauty and her other [[large breasts|"talents"]], she became known as a great beauty. With her clumsiness, her [[wardrobe malfunction]] tendencies and her obliviousness to this, she also became known as the "Lady of Destruction". It was in this state that she appeared in [[Utawarerumono: Futari no Hakuoro]] as a playable character.

title: m50_ontos
body:
The [b]M50[/b] [i][b]Ontos[/b][/i] (Greek for "thing") was an American light armored tracked anti-tank vehicle developed in the 1950s as a fast [[tank]] killer for airborne forces.

It mounted six M40 106 mm [[rocket launcher]]s as its main armament, which could be fired in rapid succession against single targets to guarantee a kill. 

The M50 was produced in limited numbers for the U.S. Marines after the U.S. Army lost interest in the project. 

The [[Marine Corps]] consistently reported excellent results when they used the Ontos for direct fire support against enemy infantry in numerous battles and operations during the [[Vietnam War]]. 

The appearance of the M50 Ontos was sometimes enough to make the Vietnamese forces break and run, and anecdotal accounts describe these enemies fleeing occupied buildings when a single spotting round fired from the M50 entered a window.

The American stock of Ontos was largely expended towards the end of the conflict and the remaining vehicles were finally removed from active service in 1969.

The Ontos inspired the design of the [[Monster Destroid]] [[mecha]] from the [[MACROSS]] science fiction series from the 1980s.

Grolla is a young woman from [[Rosenkreuzstilette]] who is easily noticeable for wearing armor as well as a white headband and a torn cloth around her legs and carrying an oversized sword to fight with, known as the Demon Sword Grollschwert, whose strength and power intensifies when its user gets weaker, and can release shockwaves. She is always calm and collected, shows loyalty to her colleagues while being guarded to everyone else, and is every bit as strict with others as she is with herself. However, if crossed in any way, she will stop at nothing to exact her revenge. She does not like sharing her thoughts with others, not even her friends. However, she is good friends with [[Sichte_Meister|Sichte Meister]], whom she holds the most dearly to. She often speaks in an old [[knight]] fashion and prefers to let her Grollschwert do the talking - in simple words, fighting first and asking questions later. She is the current posessor of Grollschwert, the previous being her grandfather.

She gets her own side game in the original game called Rosenkreuzstilette Grollschwert, where she plays a lot like [[Zero (mega man)|Zero]] from the [[Mega Man X (series)|]] and [[Mega Man Zero (series)|]] games. Her grandfather was a legendary war hero named [[Raimund Seyfarth]], who was known as Thanatos in his living days and, unbeknownst to her until she meets him at Graf Michael Sepperin's castle bridge in Grollschwert, was recently resurrected by Sepperin as a wraith resembling the [[grim_reaper|Grim Reaper]] (can also resemble [[death_(castlevania)|Death]] from [[Castlevania (series)|]]) and hired to guard the bridge. Ever since the events of the original game, she has taken up Raimund's Grollschwert to use later on, despite the fact that Raimund's spirit seems to be posessing it - therefore it seems to lead him to posess his own granddaughter every time she wields it.

A professional [[basketball]] team based in Denver, Colorado, [[United States]]. They compete in the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA) as a member of the league's Western Conference Northwest Division.

title: seisenshi_dunbine
body:
[b]Seisenshi Dunbine[/b] ([i]Sacred Warrior Dunbine[/i]), also known as [b]Aura Battler Dunbine[/b], is a [[mecha]] anime television series created by  [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]] and produced by Sunrise Studios in 1983. It also had mecha designs by [[Miyatake Kazutaka]]. 

The series is notable because it was one of the first anime mecha shows that combined medieval [[fantasy]] with [[science fiction]] [[super robot]] and real [[robot]] concepts.

The series would later inspire several OVAs, listed below
* [b][[Seisenshi Dunbine: New Story of Aura Battler Dunbine]][/b] - a sequel set in the distant future of the original series' world.
* [b][[Rean no Tsubasa]][/b] - a standalone ONA set in a separate continuity, but featuring similar setting elements. This ONA is an adaptation of Tomino's 80s novel series of the same name, which itself is an alternate Byston Well story to Dunbine.
* [b]Byston Well Monogatari: Garzey no Tsubasa[/b] - a 3-episode non-mecha fantasy OVA released in 1996, notorious for it's comically bad English dub. Also known as [b]Garzey's Wing[/b].

h4. Some mecha from the series
* [[Dunbine]]

body:
For tagging purposes this tag refers to metal [[cuffs]] used for restraint of the arms or legs, typically used in a dungeon or prison type setting when not used as an accessory. They're similar to the cuffs used under the [[handcuffs]] tag, but are depicted more solid, wider, and frequently depicted as simply a solid band of metal around the leg or arm.  They may be attached to something else, such as a wall or a [[ball and chain restraint]]. [[Oni]] are typically seen wearing shackles.

For non-metal cuffs used for the same purpose, simply use just the [[cuffs]] tag instead. The word shackles carries undertones of being locked in a dungeon or a dark room.

Unlike previous years where one or two countries play host, matches in this edition were held across 11 countries, culminating in the final at Wembley Stadium in London.

It was supposed to be held in the middle of 2020, but concerns arising from the [[coronavirus pandemic]] forced organizers to postpone the competition to mid-2021, although the short name was still kept despite change in dates.

[[Italy]] won the title by beating [[England]] in a penalty shootout 3-2 after a 1-1 draw after extra time.

title: kallen_kaslana
body:
[[Honkai Impact 3rd]] and [[Benghuai Xueyuan]] character. She was childhood friends with Otto Apocalypse, who would later become the leader of Schicksal we know today. Her father died when she was still young, killed in a fight against the Honkai. In the world of [[Honkai Impact 3rd]], Kallen was one of the descendants of [[Kevin Kaslana]] of the Previous Era.

Since then, Kallen was dedicated to protecting people from the Honkai. This raised [[otto_apocalypse|Otto]]'s fears, as he feared she would die the same way as her father.

When they grew to adults, they were betrothed, as both Kallen and Otto came from two of the influential families in Schicksal, the Kaslana family (the 'Knight') and the Apocalypse family (the 'Bishop'). Such a marriage would unite the two families. While Otto Apocalypse harboured romantic feelings for Kallen, Kallen did not reciprocate.

Within the storyline [[Yae Sakura]] and herself existed 500 years in the past with Yae rescuing Kallen after the latter washed ashore on the riverbanks of the Yae village where they developed an intimate relationship with one another.

Otto's obsession with Kallen led to an attempt to clone Kallen, eventually creating a girl he adopted as his grandaughter, [[Theresa Apocalypse]].

Voiced by [[Mizuki Nana]] with a positive, and stoic personality.

Kallen Kaslana currently has three Valkyrja forms available in-game:
* [[kallen_kaslana_(ritual_imayoh)|Ritual Imayoh]] - A fictional version of Kallen from [[Otto Apocalypse]]'s Kallen Fantasy videogames. She dons a battlesuit with heavy emphasis on ease of movement - even going as far to remove leg armour allowing her to fully maximise on her kicking combat style. She also has a pair of optical goggles around her neck for use in various situations.
* [[kallen_kaslana_(sixth_serenade)|Sixth Serenade]] - Kallen takes up the guise of shadows to fight against the false light of the Church. Sporting a purple-themed jacket, skirt, and side cut pants allowing her to be extremely fast on the battlefield. 
* [[kallen_kaslana_(sin_hunter)|SÃ¼ndenjÃ¤ger]] - An alternate Kallen from a bubble world.

In [[Benghuai Xueyuan]], Otto makes an additional clone of Kallen as an Anti-Herrscher weapon / Artifical Herrscher.

body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in the [[Gundam F91]] anime film from 1991.

[b]XM-05 Berga Giros[/b]

A high-end [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by the [[Crossbone Vanguard]]. Intended to be used by commanders, the Berga Giros was slightly reduced in size compared to its predecessor units but made up for it with more shelf nozzles for added mobility and a beefed up reactor capable of generating more power than even the SNRI's fearsome [[f91_gundam|Gundam F91]]. 

It was chiefly piloted by the Black Vanguard's captain, [[Zabine Chareux]], who had his painted in the traditional black and lilac and sported a custom Shot Lancer with extra machine guns on it.

title: zanneck

[b]ZMT-S29 Zanneck[/b]

A psycommu-enabled prototype unit by BESPA ([[Zanscare]] Imperial Army) that was fielded near the end of the Zanscare War. The Zanneck's mega beam cannon can hit targets on Earth from high in the atmosphere, or across long distances in [[space]]. The blast from this beam cannon could only be deflected by the LM314V21 [[V2 Gundam]]'s mega beam [[shield]] or its wings of light.

To compensate for the [[mobile suit]]'s low mobility when using its beam cannon, a large flight support system known as Zanneck Base was developed for its use. The Zanneck's cockpit has two seats for a pilot and a gunner.

title: leopard_2
body:
[[Germany]]'s modern main battle [[tank]]. 

While its predecessor, the [[Leopard 1]], followed a design philosophy that exchanged armor for mobility and firepower, the Leopard 2 was designed with composite armor technologies which enabled it to remain highly mobile while offering a high level of protection and firepower courtesy of its brand new 120mm gun. 

Different versions of Leopard 2s can be identified by the appearance of the turret - the Leopard 2A4 was the final variant with a boxy, square turret, while the later variants such as the 2A5 and 2A6 had wedge shaped composite screens applied to the front of the turret, giving the tank a much sharper appearance.

title: tomahawk_missile
body:
A long-range, all-weather, subsonic cruise [[missile]] used primarily by the [[United States Navy]] and [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Royal Navy]]. It is designed to be launched from [[ship]]s and [[submarine]]s and is known for its precision and versatility. The Tomahawk can carry various types of warheads, including conventional or nuclear, and it is capable of striking targets on land or at sea.

The Tomahawk missile has been in service since the 1980s and has undergone several upgrades over the years to improve its capabilities. It is often used for precision strikes against specific targets, such as enemy air defenses, communication centers, and military installations. The missile is equipped with a guidance system that allows it to navigate over long distances and engage targets with a high degree of accuracy.

The Tomahawk missile played a prominent role in various military conflicts, such as the [[Gulf War]] and the [[Iraq War]]. It is considered a key component of the [[United States]]' long-range precision strike capabilities.

In a last ditch effort to save the planet Earth, she was converted into an "Altered Human" by her father when she was 15 years old. For 10 000 years, she was responsible for healing and protecting the planet. The conversion gave her a considerably prolonged lifespan (she aged very little in the 10 000 years since conversion) and a boost to her already considerable powers.

[spoilers]At the conclusion of [i]200% Mixed Juice![/i], it is revealed [[sumika (orange juice)|Sumika]] made a simulation for a now 46 billion-year-old Suguri, now utterly bored with everything, as a means to prepare her for "something exciting."  That "something exciting" is the world of [i][[Alicianrone]][/i] where Suguri would assume the mantle of the "Forest Witch."[/spoilers]

Suguri is recognizable with her [[long_hair|long]] [[silver hair]], a [[ahoge]] and [[red eyes]] (also gained in the conversion process) as well for her lavender [[track jacket]] with an oversized [[zipper pull tab]], a [[black_skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt]] and [[black thighhighs]].

title: sora_(orange_juice)
body:
Sora is the protagonist and namesake of [i][[sora_(game)|sora]][/i].

Sora was a girl born into a grim world during a massive ongoing war that was slowly killing the planet with its skies turning dark and depressing as a result. Despite being gifted with incredible combat capabilities, she was drafted into an army against her will during her teenage years and was forced to fight in the war. After nearly dying from a mission, she was nursed back to health with refugees that defected from the war, one in particular was a man named Yukito who had a similar dream that Sora has: saving the world from the war and bring back the once beautiful skies to its former glory.

Sora has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[green eyes]]. Her usual attire during her time in the military, she is clad in a blue and yellow [[jacket]], a [[black skirt]], and [[pantyhose]]; after her defection from the war, she wears a coral-colored [[shirt]] with [[long sleeves]] and a sailor [[sailor collar]], a white skirt, and pantyhose.
